cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a new approach to practical two-party computation secure against an active adversary, which is a core topic in cryptography and security.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses an OT-based approach and gets efficiency via OT extension in the random oracle model, which involves information theory concepts.
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed protocol and introduces novel techniques for relating the outputs and inputs of OTs in a larger construction, which are related to computational complexity.
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper proposes a new approach to two-party computation and introduces novel techniques, which are related to data structures and algorithms.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper reports on an implementation of the proposed approach, which involves systems and control aspects.
